<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideed38914-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s1609"><num value="1609">§ 1609.</num><heading> Repeals</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Sections 111 to 116 of this title are repealed on the one hundred and eightieth day after <date date="1939-08-09">August 9, 1939</date>: <i>Provided, however</i>, That the notices with respect to imported alfalfa and red clover seed promulgated by the Secretary of Agriculture under the authority of sections 111 to 116 of this title, and in effect on <date date="1939-08-09">August 9, 1939</date>, shall remain with the same full force and effect as if promulgated under this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ideed38915-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1939-08-09/ch615">Aug. 9, 1939, ch. 615</ref>, title IV, § 419, <ref href="/us/stat/53/1290">53 Stat. 1290</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
